Hello,

After our explanation, customer agreed to they to gather a set of logs on Monday, but we think it would be the last one.

Also, we received a clarification regarding these two issues:

From the beginning of this case, almost all macOS users started to have issues with the Google meet when the Intercept VPN traffic ON.

Then customer figured out that if Intercept VPN traffic is disabled, the Google meet issue is solved.

But after they disabled Intercept VPN traffic, some users start complaining to the issues with Internet speed decreases.

So, on Monday customer will enable Intercept VPN traffic, and if the situation with the internet starts to be better than they will instantly check the Google Meet issue, and after that, they will collect the logs.

In this way, we will be able to investigate two cases at the same time using the one set of logs.

 



	
		
			
			Best regards,

The status of this case is follow:
If the Intercept VPN traffic is ON - customer have issues with Google Meet, that is why they disabled this option.
But, without the Intercept VPN traffic option, there is internet speed issue occurs on several computers.
And unfortunately, customer cannot enable Intercept VPN traffic there because of Google meet issue.
So, if we will fix the issue with Google meet (#429094) this issue should be fixed as well.


Best regards,
